Cool and collected; you get the impression Phillipi has seen it all, and little phases him.

One of the many designed staves by the Axis nation, these benefit the arcane caster the ability to focus more into a specific school.  Powerful and helpful; these staves prove useful for both wizard and sorcerer that seek to master their school.

Value.value: Greetings to you. Are you looking for work?
We've been dealing with orcs raiding our trade wagons for as long as we have been here. They are more than a nuisance - they are a threat to our stability.
We can only do what we've always done: send adventurers to kill their new leaders. We'll give you gold and supplies if you bring back the head of their Chosen.
Just head straight north into the frontier. If you reach the Dale, you've gone too far. Backtrack a bit and you'll find their caves.
...Ugly as ever. I'll take that, thanks. Here's the reward, as promised.
If you're still looking for something to do, Mister Snow off to the west of here has had some missing livestock, too. Head west up the road here and take the bridge north.
Having trouble finding the caves? Just go due north past the goblin-infested frontier. You'll see the orcs and likely some remains of our trade carts.

value.0: The young farmer seems intent on finishing the day's chores.

Value.value: Hey, you look like the adventuring sort. C'mere a minute.
Been having trouble with livestock going missing. Was pretty sure it was goblins again till I saw the little beasties and now I *know* it's goblins.
So if you could go north and teach them a thing or two about picking on us, that'll be a great help. It'll slow them down, at least. Hopefully.
I'd go myself, but I'm not the adventuring sort, and I'd probably just get gutted and do very little scaring 'em.
You got 'em? That's great! Here's a little something for your efforts. Really means a lot to me and my family!
Thanks a bunch for helping us out! If you'd like to find something else to do, I hear there's a fella around here looking for help finding a missing necklace.
Need something else before heading after those goblins? Just head north and then east and you'll find their stinky little lair.

value.0: A young druid who looks like she has a touch of fey blood.
This guard stands looking out towards the west and muttering something about the swamp.
Worn only by the most truthworthy guards of Cetha, this burden is not to be taken lightly.
Worn only by the most truthworthy guards of Cetha, this burden is not to be taken lightly.

A great ash tree was found growing in an ancient forest. Pure black bark and dark of leaves, its branches were exceptionally useful for the crafting of bows.

However, this practice was cut short when a group of woodcutters were found mysteriously dead under the tree, the bark stained red in their blood.  The black ash tree was soon destroyed in a fit of paranoia afterward, and now only these remain.

Value.value: *The guard looks at you distractedly, and then double-takes and turns his attention to you.*
You there. Are you going west into the swamps? If so, I could use some help.
A band of troglodytes made off with goods from a wagon which came in from Moonpier. They got their hands on a crate of valuables that had my mother's heirloom necklace in it...

It's... personal, I know. But it would really mean a lot to me if you could help me out and try to find it. It's got a distinctive appearance and you can't miss it amongst that other junk they have in those swamps.
I'll give you some gold and a cloak that'll surely help you out, if you can find the necklace and bring it back here.
That's the necklace! Thank you so much for your help. Here, as promised... *he offers over some gold and a wrapped package*
Hey, good to see you. If you're still looking for work, I know Lieutenant Phillipi is always looking for adventurous sorts.
Need help finding the swamps? Just go due west from here. Follow the road straight there. You can't imss it. I'm sure they're hiding in a hole somewhere in there.

value.0: An elder woman with a tome in hand who seems to shuffle around impatiently.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

Value.value: I am considering how I am meant to continue my research. My entire research team was killed when we went into Darkhold and I simply cannot hire more to go in to their deaths.
If I could just find someone to- Oh! You!
Yes! Perfect! I can already tell that this blood is riddled with negative energy. It will perfectly amplify my research. Thank you! Here, have your gold.

Not sure where to find Darkhold? Well, go up north on this road and turn east like you're going to look for those goblins. But there's a different entrance you'll be looking for. Not the nearby goblin cave.
Ah, the blood-gatherer! You have my thanks once again. I don't have any more projects for you, but I've heard that the Dale to the north is having troll problems, if you're looking for more work.

I have coin to hire people, but not the will to repeat what happened. Will you go to Darkhold for me? There is an entrance to a negative energy plane of some kind there, as well as rumor of a young woman who's stuck in the form of a dragon!
Get a sample of her blood for me to research and I'll pay you my stipend instead. I'd really appreciate it!

value.0: A large dwarf who works the forge with Haur.

Value.value: Hail! Sarah sent ye for one o' them recall bits, aye? Well, Master Haur jus' finished one, so ye be lucky. Take it. *he tosses a small piece of metal to you*

A simple stone plaque with the inscription: Eva's Tree.

Dogma of Chauntea:  Growing and reaping are part of the eternal cycle of the most natural part of life. Destruction for its own sake and leveling without rebuilding are anathema. Let no day pass in which you have not helped a living thing flourish. Nurture, tend, and plant wherever possible. Protect trees and plants, and save their seeds so that what is destroyed can be replaced. See to the fertility of the earth but let the human womb see to its own. Eschew fire. Plant a seed or a small plant at least once a tenday.

== Laws of the Kingdom of Cetha ==


Admittance to Frontier's Rest

    1. To enter, you are not permitted to wear a helmet or hood or use any other method to conceal your identity. Head coverings may be worn after entrance is permitted.
    2. Weapons may be carried or sheathed in city limits, provided weapons are only used in self-defense or at the direction of local law enforcement.
    3. Kingdom personnel may stop you to verify your identity against banishment lists.
    --> 3. 1. Failure to comply with requests from official personnel will result in violation of Criminal Law, point 4.

----------------------------------------


Banishment from Frontier's Rest

    The following creatures are banished and will be killed on sight:
        - Orcs
        - Trolls
        - Orogs
        - Undead
        - Yuan-Ti
        - Ogrillons
        - Lizardfolk
        - Goblinoids
        - Full-blooded Fiends

    1. Individuals listed on the Kingdom's separate banishment list will not be permitted entry.
    2. Only the Magistrate or royal family of Cetha may approve permanent banishment of individuals.
    3. Temporary banishment of 24 hours may be given by guards and official personnel of the Kingdom of Cetha.
    4. Individuals who have been banished have the right to request an appeal. Appeals will be observed by the Magistrate of Law.

----------------------------------------


Criminal Law

    1. Murder and Manslaughter.
    2. Assault.
    3. Thievery, Banditry, and Slavery.
    4. Disturbing the Public Safety and Peace.
    5. Harassment.
    6. Bribery, Extortion, and Blackmail.
    7. Public Indecency.
    8. Vandalism to Public or Private Property.


Spellcasting Law

    1. The casting of offensive spells is prohibited, except in defense of self or others, or for training purposes overseen by Kingdom personnel.
    2. Casting of defensive spells is permitted.
    3. Shapeshifting, either through magic or innate ability, into creatures listed on the banished lists is prohibited.
    --> 3. 1. The shapeshifting individual will be killed on sight.
    4. Summoned creatures may travel with their summoner.
    --> 4. 1. Summoned creatures that infringe on Criminal Law point 4 are prohibited, as determined by guard and official Kingdom personnel.
    --> 4. 2. Summoned creatures that are listed on the banished lists are prohibited and will be killed on sight.
    --> 4. 3. The summoner is responsible for all actions of the summoned creature, including any criminal actions.
